  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients who have been diagnosed with a head and/or neck cancer commonly develop oral
      mucositis (OM). The purpose of this study is to estimate the effect of Caphosol on OM and to
      evaluate if Caphosol had any effect on clinical outcomes which include quality of life, oral
      intake, swallowing function and pain.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
